data.name: SecondNoticeFooterText1
data.value:
Interest and fines will increase your debt with this Municipality, for each day of delay after the date indicated above, according to article No. 69 of the Municipal Code.

You are granted a non-extendable period of five days to appear before the Collections or Patents Office of this Municipality, in order to cancel these debts.

After this period, without the amounts owed having been paid, your account will be sent to judicial collection and later, if applicable, your property will be put up for auction according to article No. 70 of the Municipal Code. If the above occurs, you will have to go to the courts to fix your situation, in addition to the surcharge corresponding to the fees of the assigned lawyer, for the foreclosure judgment that is filed against you.
